cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with computer vision techniques for depth estimation from small motion, which is a common problem in robotics and mobile devices. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.RO (Robotics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a technique for feature extraction and optimization, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of SVD for matrix factorization, which is a common technique in machine learning and optimization, and could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
